How PitBull turned me on to rap and hip-hop....       It's kinda funny because I actually do not like rap music, no idea specifically why but it just grates on my nerves, I don't relay care for the stuff with the extreme crude lyrics like a big chunk of the women rappers and occasionally men produce. I don't mind some sex and implications in the lyrics but it seems like a lot of female rappers are competing to be the most crude. It's not always easy to understand for someone with super sensitive hearing as well when they go real fast with the music/bass really loud.        Both my brother and husband listen to it occasionally but they listen to everything...  and with the exception of Rap music I listen to pretty much every thing (rock, soul, jazz, country (classic country, all the new stuff sounds the same and it's boring sounding awful), always liked oldies, big-band, classical, the different types of Rock like classic, alternative, Punk, goth. I listen to a lot of Mexican, Puerto Rican, I really love Middle-Eastern music (specifically Turkish) and Indian music can be so beautiful and slow or crazy dancing fun, etc.). But last summer I had surgery to correct my hearing because the extreme sensitivity to sound was causing me extreme pain, stress, a lot of danger, confusion, I began having seizures when the sounds were extreme and i realized i was getting close to a dangerous psychological break-down.  So they performed a 4 hour surgery. My hearing is still much more sensitive than the normal person but it's no longer torture to walk down the street or go to a party.  Someone was playing a Pit-Bull song and I liked it and she told me who it was and played me another song. So now she's being sending me music of both American and foreign rappers that people heavy rap, calmer rap, rap/rock mix (which i really like now!) Hip-hop and the other forms. With the extreme sensitivity to whatever it was with the rap music gone in enjoying it. I love dancing and have danced competitively of and on since I was a young child and the rap and hip-hop is fun to dance to now that i can handle it.      So, Pitbull.... Thanks for being just what I needed to hear!!!
